target: map
validations:
  - name: pathfinding_correctness
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the A* pathfinding implementation returns correct shortest paths.
        Test cases: (1) straight-line path on open grass returns a direct route,
        (2) path around a water obstacle routes correctly without crossing water,
        (3) path to an unreachable tile (surrounded by water) returns null,
        (4) diagonal movement costs sqrt(2) times the tile cost, not 1.0,
        (5) diagonal moves are blocked when an adjacent cardinal tile is not walkable
        (no corner cutting). The heuristic must be admissible (octile distance for
        8-directional movement).

  - name: placement_validation
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify isValidPlacement correctly rejects: (1) placements that extend
        beyond map bounds, (2) placements overlapping water tiles, (3) placements
        overlapping the entrance gate, (4) placements overlapping existing enclosures,
        (5) placements overlapping PATH tiles. It must accept valid placements on
        grass or dirt tiles that do not overlap any obstacle or existing enclosure.
        The function must return a reason string for rejections.

  - name: map_initialization
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify initMap() creates a 40x30 grid where: (1) the entrance gate occupies
        at least one tile on the left edge near row 15, (2) a PATH extends from the
        entrance inward, (3) all remaining tiles default to GRASS, (4) a few
        decorative water features exist at fixed positions, (5) every tile value
        is a valid TILE constant (0-4). The grid dimensions must be exactly
        MAP_COLS x MAP_ROWS.

  - name: coordinate_conversion
    type: agent_validation
    severity: warning
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that tileToPixel and pixelToTile are exact inverses:
        pixelToTile(tileToPixel(c, r)) must return {col: c, row: r} for all valid
        tile coordinates. Also verify that screenToTile correctly incorporates the
        camera offset, so clicking at screen position (x, y) with camera at (cx, cy)
        maps to the tile at world position (x + cx, y + cy).
